headline: Palantir Co-Founder Peter Thiel On How Elon Musk Conquered Both Automobiles And Space—And Why He'd 'Never Bet' Against The Tesla CEO
summary: At LAUNCH Festival 2015, Peter Thiel offered insights into how Elon Musk simultaneously transformed the auto and aerospace industries through Tesla Inc. and SpaceX. What Happened: In a conversation with Jason Calacanis, Thiel explained that Musk succeeded partly by choosing “weak competition.” He noted that while traditional car companies and the U.S. aerospace sector had “barely innovated in 50 years,” Musk entered these industries with strategic foresight. headline: PayPal once again lets you pool money from others to pay for things together
summary: PayPal is launching a few features that let users in groups pool money with friends or family, to collectively pay for trips, travels, gifts, and anything else. The company is launching this feature in the U.S., Germany, the U.K., Italy, and Spain ahead of the holiday season. headline: PayPal Unveils Innovative Money Pooling Feature, Simplifying Group Expenses Between Family and Friends
summary: Today, PayPal announced a new experience that gives customers an easy way to pool money with friends and family for group gifts, travel, special events or other shared expenses. Rolling out globally across the US, Germany, Italy and Spain, the new experience gives customers the ability to set up a pool in the PayPal app or online, invite friends and family to contribute, track group contributions and transfer funds to their PayPal balance to spend or withdraw.
